# Universal Code Quality Rules

## ✅ Universal Code Quality Rules (All Languages)
- Max 2 levels of nesting (if / else / loop)
- Follow YAGNI principle
- Functions should be small & single-purpose (<30 lines)
- No magic values → use let/const or named constants
- Use intention-revealing names for vars, funcs, classes
- Avoid silent catch blocks — log or explicitly handle
- Avoid duplicating state across local/props/context
- Add `// TODO(name, date)` or `# TODO(name, date)` for hacks
- No unnecessary fallbacks — document if needed
- Expensive loops or filters must be memoized or paginated

## Language-Specific Guidelines

### 🐍 Python-Specific
- Explicit is better than implicit. Don't hide behavior in dunder methods or decorators unless standard
- Use typing for all public functions/classes. Especially return values
- Don't mutate arguments in-place. Always return new values unless explicitly designed to do so
- Use dataclasses or Pydantic for structured data, not loose dicts
- Group related functions into modules, not long files
- Use `__all__` or single-point exports. Avoid accidental public exposure
- Don't catch Exception broadly. Use specific error types
- Use pathlib and logging instead of os.path and print
- Stick to black and ruff/flake8 for style and linting

### 🍎 Swift-Specific
- Avoid force unwrapping (!) — always use guard let, if let, or default values
- Use struct by default, only use class if you need reference semantics
- Functions should return immutable values unless you're explicitly mutating state
- Favor value types (struct/enums) + protocol conformance
- Avoid deep optional chaining — prefer early returns with guard
- Use private(set) or internal access control to encapsulate state
- Group related code using extensions — keeps logic modular and discoverable
- Use @MainActor or concurrency annotations clearly
- Use SwiftLint for consistent style, mark temporary disables with `// swiftlint:disable [rule] // TODO(name, date)`

### 🌐 JavaScript/TypeScript-Specific
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Prefer const over let, avoid var entirely
- Use async/await over Promise chains
- Destructure objects and arrays for clarity
- Use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??)
- Prefer pure functions and immutable data structures
- Use meaningful variable names, avoid abbreviations
- Use ESLint and Prettier for consistent formatting
- Handle errors explicitly, don't ignore Promise rejections

### 📱 React Native/Expo-Specific
- Use Expo Router for navigation instead of React Navigation directly
- Prefer `useRouter()` over `useNavigation()` for Expo Router
- Use `expo-constants` for environment variables, not `process.env`
- Use `expo-linking` for deep links and URL handling
- Prefer `expo-image` over `react-native` Image for better performance
- Use `expo-status-bar` for status bar management
- Handle platform differences with `Platform.OS` checks
- Use `expo-device` for device information instead of custom solutions
- Prefer `expo-sqlite` over `react-native-sqlite-storage`
- Use `expo-secure-store` for sensitive data, not AsyncStorage
- Handle keyboard with `expo-keyboard` for better UX
- Use `expo-haptics` for tactile feedback
- Prefer `expo-font` for custom fonts over manual font loading
- Use `expo-splash-screen` for proper splash screen handling
- Handle app state with `expo-app-state` instead of custom listeners

### ☕ Java-Specific
- Follow standard naming conventions (PascalCase for classes, camelCase for methods)
- Use final keyword for variables that shouldn't change
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use Optional for nullable return types
- Handle exceptions appropriately, don't catch and ignore
- Use StringBuilder for string concatenation in loops
- Follow single responsibility principle for classes
- Use dependency injection instead of static dependencies

### 🗄️ Supabase-Specific
- Always use RLS (Row Level Security) policies for data access control
- Use `supabase.from('table').select()` instead of raw SQL when possible
- Implement proper error handling for Supabase client operations
- Use `supabase.auth.getUser()` for authentication checks
- Prefer Edge Functions over database functions for complex logic
- Use `supabase.storage.from('bucket')` for file operations
- Implement proper connection pooling with `supabase.createClient()`
- Use `supabase.realtime` for real-time subscriptions
- Always validate input with Zod schemas before Supabase operations
- Use `supabase.rpc()` for custom database functions
- Implement proper transaction handling with `supabase.transaction()`
- Use `supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange()` for auth state management
- Prefer `supabase.from().upsert()` over separate insert/update operations
- Use `supabase.from().select().single()` for single record queries
- Implement proper pagination with `supabase.from().select().range()`

## 🧪 Universal Testing Guidelines
- Always run tests before and after any code changes
- Write tests for new features before implementation (TDD)
- Update tests when changing existing behavior
- Never commit broken tests — fix or skip with TODO
- Use descriptive test names that explain the scenario
- Test both success and failure cases
- Mock external dependencies (APIs, databases, file system)
- Use test data factories for consistent test data
- Keep tests fast (<2 minutes total runtime)
- Group related tests using test classes or describe blocks

## 🔐 Authentication Testing
- Always test with real authentication tokens for API endpoints
- Use environment variables for test credentials
- Test both authenticated and unauthenticated scenarios
- Validate token expiration and refresh flows
- Test permission-based access control
- Mock authentication in unit tests, use real auth in integration tests

## 📊 Test Coverage Targets
- **Service Layer**: 70-85%
- **API Layer**: 60-75%
- **Models/Utils**: 85-95%
- **Infrastructure**: 50-70%
- **Frontend Components**: 60-80%
- **Critical Business Logic**: 90%+

## 🚀 Framework-Specific Quick Commands (CUSTOMIZE FOR YOUR STACK)

### Backend Testing
```bash
# Full test suite (Fastify/TypeScript)
cd apps/orchestrator && pnpm test # vitest with TypeScript
cd apps/orchestrator && pnpm test --coverage # coverage report

# Service layer tests
cd apps/orchestrator && pnpm test src/agents/ # test specific agents

# API tests with authentication
export SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=$(grep 'SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=' .env | cut -d'=' -f2)
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_ANON_KEY" http://localhost:3001/healthz

# Single test file
cd apps/orchestrator && pnpm test src/agents/composer.test.ts

# Debug failing tests
cd apps/orchestrator && pnpm test --reporter=verbose
```

### Frontend Testing (React Native/Expo)
```bash
# Mobile app health checks
cd apps/mobile && expo doctor # check for issues
cd apps/mobile && expo install --check # verify dependencies

# Production build testing
cd apps/mobile && expo build --platform android --type apk
cd apps/mobile && expo build --platform ios --type archive

# Development testing
cd apps/mobile && expo start --no-dev --minify # production build test
cd apps/mobile && expo start --tunnel # test with tunnel
cd apps/mobile && expo start --dev-client # test with dev client

# Platform-specific testing
cd apps/mobile && npx react-native run-android --variant=debug
cd apps/mobile && npx react-native run-ios --configuration Debug

# EAS Build testing
cd apps/mobile && eas build --platform android --profile preview
cd apps/mobile && eas build --platform ios --profile preview

# Mobile-specific testing commands
cd apps/mobile && expo start --android # Android emulator
cd apps/mobile && expo start --ios # iOS simulator
cd apps/mobile && expo start --web # Web version testing
```

### Supabase Testing
```bash
# Supabase CLI testing
supabase status # check local development status
supabase db reset # reset local database
supabase db diff # check for schema changes
supabase functions serve # test Edge Functions locally

# Database testing
supabase db test # run database tests
supabase db lint # check for database issues
supabase db seed # seed test data

# Edge Function testing
supabase functions deploy --no-verify-jwt # deploy functions
supabase functions logs --follow # monitor function logs

# RLS Policy testing
supabase db diff --schema public # check RLS policies
supabase db lint --schema public # validate RLS setup

# Authentication testing
supabase auth test # test auth configuration
supabase auth users list # list test users
```

## 🔧 Authentication Token Management (CUSTOMIZE FOR YOUR AUTH SYSTEM)

### Get Test Authentication Token
```bash
# From environment file
export SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=$(grep 'SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=' .env | cut -d'=' -f2)

# Or generate new token via Supabase API
curl -X POST https://your-project.supabase.co/auth/v1/token \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email": "test@example.com", "password": "testpassword"}'
```

### Use Authentication Token in Tests
```bash
# API testing with real auth
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_ANON_KEY" \
  http://localhost:3001/healthz

# Language-specific test with real auth (TypeScript example)
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'

const supabase = createClient(
  process.env.SUPABASE_URL!,
  process.env.SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
)
const { data, error } = await supabase.from('profiles').select('*')
```

